{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0181DMH7MoNUmcSCK8CMK5EF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clean. Here is the summary.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Files reviewed:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` (195 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` (191 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/index.ts` (barrel exports)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-validator.test.ts` (527 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` (697 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` (63 lines)\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **HIGH — Operator precedence ambiguity in `checkVerificationTools`**: The `&&`/`||` chain lacked parentheses. While functionally correct due to JS precedence rules, this was a readability/maintainability hazard. Refactored to extract `hasApt`/`hasApk` checks and add explicit parentheses.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — Redundant double-read in `checkInfrastructure`**: `dimensions.ts` read the Dockerfile itself (existsSync, readFileSync, FROM parsing) and then called `validateDockerfile()` which did the exact same reads. Refactored `checkInfrastructure` to delegate entirely to `validateDockerfile()` and dispatch on its error messages. Removed unused `readFileSync` import.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — Missing test for `COPY --from=` binary detection (AC #2)**: Added test `passes with COPY --from (multi-stage)` (auto-applied by linter).\n\n4. **MEDIUM — `checkNoSourceCopy` false negative with COPY flags**: The regex `COPY\\s+src/` would not match `COPY --chown=node src/`. Updated pattern to `COPY\\s+(?:--\\S+\\s+)*src/` to handle optional flags (auto-applied by linter). Added test for `COPY --chown` edge case.\n\n**Updated tests** in `dimensions.test.ts` to match refactored `checkInfrastructure` — all infrastructure tests now mock `validateDockerfile` directly instead of FS calls. Removed unused `readFileSync` mock variable.\n\n**Results:**\n- Build: pass\n- Tests: 2817 passed, 0 failed (109 files)\n- Coverage: 96.99% overall (target: 90%), all 120 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Story status: updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains\n- MEDIUM: Redundant double-read of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`\n- MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown=node src/` and similar flag patterns — regex updated\n- MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern — test added\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `checkVerificationTools` loose matching: `content.includes(tool)` matches the tool name anywhere in the file (comments, paths, variable names), not just in install commands. Acceptable per dev notes (\"false positives are acceptable — advisory tool, not a security gate\") but could cause confusion.\n- `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number in its gap — unlike `checkPinnedFrom` and `checkNoSourceCopy` which report line numbers. Not a bug but inconsistent.\n- `dfGap` helper creates an extra object spread when `line` is defined — minor allocation overhead, no real impact.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage on `validateDockerfile` rule flags: paths where `rules.requirePinnedFrom` etc. are `false` are untested since `DEFAULT_RULES` always enables all rules. Not exercisable without exposing a way to inject custom rules.\n- No test for `COPY test/` pattern (only `src/` and `lib/` are tested for source copy detection).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Clean separation between validator and audit dimension. Barrel exports respected. Result<T> pattern followed consistently.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1b523bf08ec8746b (use SendMessage with to: 'a1b523bf08ec8746b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76407\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 279843</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef2f2ce5-c013-4ad4-b6dd-a80c40f8ca85","uuid":"626d41e9-4853-4027-bca6-176ec5095f41","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:27:56.555Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a1b523bf08ec8746b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clean. Here is the summary.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Files reviewed:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` (195 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` (191 lines)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/index.ts` (barrel exports)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src