{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UW1sQ7u6vwWsy2JqyFga9Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UBCfeR2L9Z6rfNb3PdVmCH","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.","new_string":"- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — code-review (2026-03-21T05:32Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\n- **Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":364,"cache_read_input_tokens":47621,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":364},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_