{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Px9QykcT3xZH5Ma3bgdnzG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HuQt3gmssqTRF9EpkD9Qr9","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"STORY_CONTENT=$(cat /tmp/codeharness-verify-4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation/story.md)\n\n# Build prompt using the template structure\nPROMPT=\"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Here is its content:\n\n---\n${STORY_CONTENT}\n---\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion:\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n- Example: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version\n- Example: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness audit --json\n\nThe container has: codeharness, claude, curl, jq, node, npm installed.\n\n### Verification Strategy for This Story\n\nThis story adds Dockerfile validation rules to the audit command. The key verification approaches:\n\n- **AC 1:** Check that patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md exists in the container and lists the 6 required elements\n- **AC 2-3, 5-8:** Create test Dockerfiles inside the container with specific violations, then run codeharness audit --json to verify the right gaps are reported. Use the audit infrastructure dimension results.\n- **AC 4:** Create a Dockerfile that passes all rules and verify audit reports infrastructure: pass\n- **AC 9:** Run codeharness audit --json and verify the infrastructure dimension reports all 6 rule categories\n- **AC 10:** Temporarily rename/remove the rules file, run audit, and verify it uses defaults with a warning\n\nTo create test Dockerfiles, use docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/testproject && cat > /tmp/testproject/Dockerfile << EOF ... EOF' then run docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/testproject && codeharness audit --json'\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- docker exec codeharness-verify <cli-command> [args]\n- Capture exit codes: docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c '<command>; echo EXIT:\\$?'\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery from HOST (not container):\n- VictoriaLogs: http://localhost:9428\n- VictoriaMetrics: http://localhost:8428\n- VictoriaTraces: http://localhost:16686\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n## AC N: <description>\n\n\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\n\n\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\n\n**Verdict:** PASS | FAIL | [ESCALATE]\n\nIMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. ALL commands MUST use docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Do NOT access source code — no src/ directory exists\n3. Report REAL failures — never fabricate evidence\n4. Every AC needs functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence\n5. Verify aggressively, escalate narrowly\n6. [ESCALATE] is ONLY for things genuinely impossible to automate\n7. Never switch to unit-testable verification\"\n\ncd /tmp/codeharness-verify-4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"$PROMPT\" 2>&1","description":"Run black-box verifier session","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":202,"cache_read_input_tokens":59077,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":202},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef2f2ce5-c013-4ad4-b6dd-a80c40f8ca85","uuid":"30bf0dd7-d27f-4c5e-9827-d8b5a4f6d46d"}
