{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ABQbFNgsXHqrmE6AURUgQ2","type":"tool_result","content":"285:## AC 10: Missing dockerfile-rules.md uses defaults with warning\n286-\n287-```bash\n288-docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mv /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md.bak && cd /tmp/testproject && cat > Dockerfile << \"EOF\"\n289-FROM node:latest\n290-CMD [\"node\"]\n291-EOF\n292-codeharness audit --json 2>&1 | tail -1'\n293-```\n294-\n295-```output\n296-{...,\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile exists (6 issues)\",\"gaps\":[\n297-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"unpinned base image -- use specific version.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Pin node:latest to a specific version tag\"},\n298-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"project binary not installed.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add npm install -g, pip install, or COPY --from to install the project binary\"},\n299-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"verification tool missing: curl\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Install curl via apt-get install or apk add\"},\n300-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"verification tool missing: jq\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Install jq via apt-get install or apk add\"},\n301-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"no non-root USER instruction found.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add USER <non-root-user> instruction (e.g., USER node)\"},\n302-  {\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"no cache cleanup detected.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add cache cleanup: rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*, npm cache clean --force, or pip cache purge\"}\n303-]},...}\n304-```\n305-\n306-Additionally checked full non-JSON output:\n307-\n308-```bash\n309-docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/testproject && codeharness audit 2>&1'\n310-```\n311-\n312-```output\n313-[WARN] State indicates c8 but no Vitest/c8 found in project — re-detecting\n314-[WARN] No Node.js coverage tool detected\n315-[WARN] observability: static: skipped (analysis failed), runtime: skipped (validation failed)\n316-  ...\n317-[WARN] infrastructure: Dockerfile exists (6 issues)\n318-  [WARN] unpinned base image -- use specific version. -- fix: Pin node:latest to a specific version tag\n319-  [WARN] project binary not installed. -- fix: ...\n320-  [WARN] verification tool missing: curl -- fix: ...\n321-  [WARN] verification tool missing: jq -- fix: ...\n322-  [WARN] no non-root USER instruction found. -- fix: ...\n323-  [WARN] no cache cleanup detected. -- fix: ...\n324-```\n325-\n326-**Analysis:** With `dockerfile-rules.md` removed, validation still works correctly — all 6 rule categories are checked and gaps reported using hardcoded defaults. However, the specific warning message `\"dockerfile-rules.md not found -- using defaults.\"` is NOT visible in either JSON or text output. The defaults are silently applied.\n327-\n328-**Partial evidence:** Defaults work correctly (validated by all 6 categories still being checked). Warning message not surfaced in CLI output.\n329-\n330-**Verdict:** FAIL — defaults work correctly but the required warning message \"dockerfile-rules.md not found -- using defaults.\" is not reported in the output.\n331-\n332-Rules file was restored after test:\n333-```bash\n334-docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mv /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md.bak /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md'\n335-```\n336-\n337----\n338-\n339-## Summary\n340-\n341-| AC | Description | Verdict |\n342-|----|-------------|---------|\n343-| 1 | dockerfile-rules.md lists 6 required elements | PASS |\n344-| 2 | Missing binary reports \"project binary not installed.\" | PASS |\n345-| 3 | FROM node:latest reports \"unpinned base image -- use specific version.\" | PASS |"}]},"par